President Biden visited Dawson Springs, Kentucky, to assess the damage caused by the recent tornadoes. During his visit, he met with local residents, including a soon-to-be graduate from the University of Kentucky, and promised to provide support and assistance to the affected communities. He expressed his condolences for the lives lost and praised the resilience and compassion of the people in the face of the disaster. The President also announced that the federal government will cover 100% of the costs for the first 30 days of emergency work, including debris removal and emergency services. He emphasized the need for mental health support for those affected and encouraged people to seek assistance through FEMA. President Biden assured the community that they will recover and rebuild, and promised to provide all necessary resources for the recovery efforts.